title: Did Sinema Have ‘Let Them Eat Cake’ Moment While Voting Against Raising Minimum Wage?
subtitle: Some compared her to the last queen of France before the French Revolution.
author: Bethania Palma
vclaim: U.S. Sen. Krysten Sinema brought cake to the Senate when she voted against including a federal minimum wage increase in a $1.9 trillion COVID-19 relief package, prompting comparisons to Marie Antoinette's alleged remark about her impoverished subjects, "Let them eat cake."
